{"calories":"840","carbs":null,"category":{"badge_name":"","display_name":"Dinner","display_order":1,"is_filterable":false,"insight_segment_slug":"main-recipe-ratings","slug":"main"},"choices_available":[],"description":"When we hear the words “baked pasta,” coziness, movie marathons, and lots of cheese immediately come to mind. Instead of the classic ziti, we swapped in penne noodles, which manage to soak up even more deliciousness in their outside ridges. Tossed with crispy roasted mushrooms, creamy ricotta, and a quick homemade tomato sauce, the pasta is smothered in mozzarella and baked until gooey. If that’s not 5 star comfort food, we’re not sure what is. ","difficulty":"medium","external_id":"d87b9ee9c9","fat":null,"images":[{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17423/1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0023_1.jpg","size":"full","type":"portrait"}},{"image":{"url":"/assets/blank_profile-62376be1ebee267193d25c20f8cd8bc5a6c47743a4a323d32a54ecdf231b7b80.png","size":"large_cropped","type":"main_cropped"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17425/1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0031.jpg","size":"full","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17425/menu_small_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0031.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"card"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"full","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/hero_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"hero","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/menu_small_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"medium-rectangle","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/small_square_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"small-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/medium_square_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"medium-square","type":"main"}},{"image":{"url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/17420/recipe_profile_page_1961_Baked_Penne_with_Mushroom_Ragu_and_Ricotta___0021_1.jpg","size":"large-rectangle","type":"main"}}],"name":"Baked Penne with Roasted Mushrooms and Ricotta","novice_time":null,"portion_count":2,"prep_time":"40-50","pro_time":null,"product_type":{"slug":"subscription","included_in_subscription":true},"protein":null,"public_slug":"baked-penne-with-mushroom-ragout-and-ricotta","pdf_url":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/public_uploads/recipe/region_schedule/downloadable_recipe_card/9890/recipe_card20161228-4-12ipwwx.pdf","recipe_id":1961,"type":"regular","servings":2,"short_name":"Baked Penne","subtitle":"with Roasted Mushrooms and Ricotta","title":"Baked Penne","legal_copy_short":null,"available_for_non_sub":false,"additional_price":"0","cooking_tip":"\u003cp\u003eBe sure to read through the entire recipe before you begin cooking. Trust us—you'll be glad you did!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eWiping mushrooms clean instead of rinsing prevents them from absorbing water. They won't brown well if they're too wet.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003eStarchy pasta cooking water will give your sauce a perfect consistency and help it to cling to the noodles. Keep adding it until the sauce is silky—you may need more than you think.\u003c/p\u003e","equipment":["10\" large pot with lid","baking sheet","10\" medium high-sided pan"],"id":1961,"ingredients":["red onion","garlic","parsley","tomato paste","red wine","14-ounce can chopped tomatoes","penne pasta","grated Parmesan cheese","ricotta cheese","shredded mozzarella cheese","8\" aluminum tin","shiitake mushrooms","cremini mushrooms","oyster mushrooms"],"ingredients_full":[{"name":"red onion","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":1,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/90/medium_square_red-onion-cut-half.jpg"},{"name":"garlic","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"clove","displayOrder":2,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/2/medium_square_GARLIC_PEELED_copy.jpg"},{"name":"parsley","quantity":"0.125","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":3,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1279/medium_square_medium_square_parsley-test.jpg"},{"name":"tomato paste","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"tablespoon","displayOrder":4,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/134/medium_square_TOMATO_PASTE_copy.jpg"},{"name":"red wine","quantity":"0.25","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":5,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/209/medium_square_RED_COOKING_WINE.jpg"},{"name":"14-ounce can chopped tomatoes","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":6,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1459/medium_square_medium_square_crushed-tomatoes.jpg"},{"name":"penne pasta","quantity":"8.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":7,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/428/medium_square_BARILLA_PENNE_PASTA_copy.jpg"},{"name":"grated Parmesan cheese","quantity":"0.33","measurementUnit":"cup","displayOrder":8,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/22/medium_square_parmesan-cheese-2.jpg"},{"name":"ricotta cheese","quantity":"5.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":9,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/1486/medium_square_RICOTTA_CHEESE_-4386_copy.jpg"},{"name":"shredded mozzarella cheese","quantity":"3.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":10,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/532/medium_square_shredded-cheese-moz.jpg"},{"name":"8\" aluminum tin","quantity":"1.0","measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":11,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/830/medium_square_square_baking_tin.jpg"},{"name":"shiitake mushrooms","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":100,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/221/medium_square_shiitake-mushrooms-test.jpg"},{"name":"cremini mushrooms","quantity":"4.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":100,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/326/medium_square_cremini-mushrooms-test2.jpg"},{"name":"oyster mushrooms","quantity":"2.0","measurementUnit":"ounce","displayOrder":100,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/609/medium_square_oyster-mushrooms.jpg"}],"is_tastemaker":false,"upgradeable":false,"is_holiday_hack":false,"pantry_items":["kosher salt","black pepper"],"pantry_items_full":[{"name":"kosher salt","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":16,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/473/medium_square_kosher-salt.jpg"},{"name":"black pepper","quantity":null,"measurementUnit":"","displayOrder":17,"imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/recipe/ingredient/image/493/medium_square_spice-black-pepper-test.jpg"}],"steps":[{"title":"Prepare Ingredients ","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15865/recipe_card_size_1._Prepare_Ingredients_2X_3X.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003ePreheat oven to 450℉. Cover a large pot of water and bring to a boil over high heat (covering the pot helps it boil faster without the water evaporating!). Peel \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e, halve, and thinly slice. Wipe \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e clean with a damp paper towel and roughly chop, discarding stems (see Recipe Tip). Mince \u003cstrong\u003egarlic\u003c/strong\u003e. Rinse \u003cstrong\u003eparsley \u003c/strong\u003eand roughly chop leaves, discarding stems.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Roast Mushrooms ","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15868/recipe_card_size_2._Roast_Mushrooms_2X.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eOn a baking sheet, toss \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e with \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003epepper\u003c/strong\u003e as desired. Roast until browned and crispy, about 15 minutes. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Make Sauce ","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15867/recipe_card_size_3._Simmer_Sauce.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eHeat \u003cstrong\u003e1 tablespoon olive oil \u003c/strong\u003ein a medium high-sided pan over medium heat. When oil is shimmering, add \u003cstrong\u003eonion\u003c/strong\u003e and cook until very soft, about 8 minutes. Add \u003cstrong\u003etomato paste \u003c/strong\u003eand \u003cstrong\u003egarlic \u003c/strong\u003eand cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes more. Add \u003cstrong\u003ewine\u003c/strong\u003e and cook until reduced by half, 1-2 minutes. Add \u003cstrong\u003echopped tomatoes and their juices \u003c/strong\u003eand bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and cook until softened, 5 minutes more. Season with \u003cstrong\u003e.25 teaspoon salt\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003epepper \u003c/strong\u003eas desired.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Cook Penne","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15866/recipe_card_size_4._Cook_Penne.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eWhile sauce cooks, generously season boiling water with \u003cstrong\u003esalt\u003c/strong\u003e. Stir in \u003cstrong\u003epenne \u003c/strong\u003eand cook, uncovered, until almost al dente, about 8 minutes. Reserve \u003cstrong\u003e.5 cup pasta cooking water\u003c/strong\u003e, then drain.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Assemble Pasta ","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15869/recipe_card_size_5._Assemble_Pasta_2XB.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eStir \u003cstrong\u003eParmesan\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003emushrooms\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003ehalf of parsley\u003c/strong\u003e into tomato sauce over medium heat. Add \u003cstrong\u003epenne\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003ereserved pasta cooking water\u003c/strong\u003e, 1 tablespoon at a time, until sauce is thick and clings to noodles (see Recipe Tip). Pour \u003cstrong\u003epenne and sauce\u003c/strong\u003e into aluminum tin. Wipe baking sheet from mushrooms clean and place tin on baking sheet. Dollop \u003cstrong\u003ericotta \u003c/strong\u003eover pasta, then sprinkle over \u003cstrong\u003emozzarella\u003c/strong\u003e.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e"},{"title":"Bake Pasta","imageUrl":"//dusyefwqqyfwe.cloudfront.net/uploads/culinary/recipe_image/file/15870/recipe_card_size_6._Plate_Pasta.jpg","description":"\u003cp\u003eBake until cheese is golden brown on top, 5-7 minutes. Remove \u003cstrong\u003ebaked penne\u003c/strong\u003e from oven, divide between serving plates, and garnish with \u003cstrong\u003eremaining parsley\u003c/strong\u003e. Dig into your gorgeous homemade meal!\u003c/p\u003e"}],"tags":{"all":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"allergens":[{"name":"Milk","slug":"milk","hex_color":""},{"name":"Wheat","slug":"wheat","hex_color":""}],"proteins":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""},{"name":"Pasta","slug":"pasta","hex_color":""}],"publicFacing":[{"name":"vegetarian","slug":"vegetarian","hex_color":""}],"feature":[]}}